## Architectural Principle

### "One Endpoint Per Capability, Not Per Provider"

**Core Rule**: Create generic endpoints that route based on parameters (model name, provider name), not separate endpoints for each provider.

### Why This Pattern?

✅ **Scalability**: Add 100+ providers without code changes  
✅ **Consistency**: Single point for auth, rate limiting, logging  
✅ **Maintainability**: One endpoint to debug and monitor  
✅ **Industry Standard**: Follows OpenAI's API design  
✅ **Future-Proof**: Easy to add caching, metrics, circuit breakers

---

## Endpoint Categories

### Category 1: LLM Capabilities (Model-Based Routing)

**Use Case**: Different AI models from different providers

**Pattern**: `/api/v1/{capability}/{action}`

**Routing Logic**: Model parameter → Provider detection → API routing

| Endpoint | Purpose | Models Supported |
|----------|---------|------------------|
| `/api/v1/chat/completions` | Text generation | gpt-4, claude-4-sonnet, gemini-2.0, o1-preview, llama-3 |
| `/api/v1/images/generate` | Image generation | dall-e-3, imagen-3, sdxl-1.0 |
| `/api/v1/embeddings/generate` | Text embeddings | text-embedding-3-large, textembedding-gecko |
| `/api/v1/audio/transcribe` | Speech-to-text | whisper-1, chirp-3 |
| `/api/v1/audio/speech` | Text-to-speech | tts-1, tts-1-hd |

### Category 2: External Tools (Config-Based Routing)

**Use Case**: External APIs/MCPs with different actions

**Pattern**: `/api/v1/mcp/:provider/:action`

**Routing Logic**: Provider config → Action config → API routing

| Provider | Actions | Base URL |
|----------|---------|----------|
| tavily | search, extract | https://api.tavily.com |
| serper | search | https://google.serper.dev |
| browserless | screenshot, pdf | https://chrome.browserless.io |
| firecrawl | scrape, crawl | https://api.firecrawl.dev |

---

## Model-Based Routing

### How It Works

```javascript
// 1. Client sends request with model parameter
POST /api/v1/chat/completions
{
  "model": "claude-4-sonnet",
  "messages": [...]
}

// 2. Gateway detects provider from model name
function detectProvider(model) {
  if (model.startsWith('gpt-') || model.startsWith('o1-')) return 'openai';
  if (model.startsWith('claude-')) return 'anthropic';
  if (model.startsWith('gemini-')) return 'google';
  if (model.startsWith('llama')) return 'ollama';
  return null;
}

// 3. Gateway fetches API key for detected provider
const apiKey = await fetchKey(provider, serviceId, projectId);

// 4. Gateway routes to provider's API
const response = await routeToProvider(provider, model, request, apiKey);

// 5. Gateway returns unified response
res.json(response);
```

### Provider Detection Rules

```javascript
// OpenAI
'gpt-4', 'gpt-4-turbo', 'gpt-4o', 'gpt-3.5-turbo'
'o1-preview', 'o1-mini'  // Deep research models
'dall-e-2', 'dall-e-3'    // Image generation
'whisper-1', 'tts-1'      // Audio models

// Anthropic
'claude-4-sonnet', 'claude-3-5-sonnet', 'claude-3-haiku'

// Google
'gemini-2.0-flash', 'gemini-1.5-pro', 'gemini-1.5-flash'
'imagen-3', 'textembedding-gecko'

// Stability AI
'sdxl-1.0', 'sd-3.5-large', 'sd-ultra'

// Ollama (Local)
'llama3', 'mistral', 'mixtral', 'codellama'
```

### Implementation Template

```javascript
externalApp.post('/api/v1/{capability}/{action}', authenticateExternal, async (req, res) => {
  try {
    const { model, ...params } = req.body;
    const serviceId = req.headers['x-service-id'] || 'default';
    const projectId = req.headers['x-project-id'] || 'default';
    
    // 1. Detect provider from model
    const provider = detectProvider(model);
    if (!provider) {
      return res.status(400).json({ error: `Unsupported model: ${model}` });
    }
    
    // 2. Fetch API key from AI Inferencing service
    const apiKey = await fetchProviderKey(provider, projectId, serviceId);
    
    // 3. Route to provider-specific handler
    const response = await routeToProvider(provider, model, params, apiKey);
    
    // 4. Return response
    res.json(response);
  } catch (error) {
    console.error(`[{Capability}] Error:`, error.message);
    res.status(500).json({ error: error.message });
  }
});
```

