## Examples

### Example 1: Chat Completions (Multiple Providers)

```bash
# OpenAI GPT-4
curl -X POST http://localhost:8777/api/v1/chat/completions \
  -H "X-Service-ID: my-app" \
  -H "X-Project-ID: my-project" \
  -d '{
    "model": "gpt-4",
    "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "Hello"}]
  }'

# Anthropic Claude
curl -X POST http://localhost:8777/api/v1/chat/completions \
  -H "X-Service-ID: my-app" \
  -H "X-Project-ID: my-project" \
  -d '{
    "model": "claude-4-sonnet",
    "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "Hello"}]
  }'

# OpenAI o1 (Deep Research)
curl -X POST http://localhost:8777/api/v1/chat/completions \
  -H "X-Service-ID: my-app" \
  -H "X-Project-ID: my-project" \
  -d '{
    "model": "o1-preview",
    "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "Explain quantum computing"}]
  }'
```

### Example 2: Image Generation (Multiple Providers)

```bash
# OpenAI DALL-E 3
curl -X POST http://localhost:8777/api/v1/images/generate \
  -H "X-Service-ID: my-app" \
  -d '{
    "model": "dall-e-3",
    "prompt": "A sunset over mountains",
    "size": "1024x1024"
  }'

# Google Imagen 3
curl -X POST http://localhost:8777/api/v1/images/generate \
  -H "X-Service-ID: my-app" \
  -d '{
    "model": "imagen-3",
    "prompt": "A sunset over mountains"
  }'
```

### Example 3: MCP Web Search (Config-Based)

```bash
# Tavily Search
curl -X POST http://localhost:8777/api/v1/mcp/tavily/search \
  -H "X-Service-ID: goose-agent" \
  -H "X-Project-ID: ai-workspace" \
  -d '{
    "query": "latest AI developments",
    "max_results": 5
  }'

# Serper Google Search
curl -X POST http://localhost:8777/api/v1/mcp/serper/search \
  -H "X-Service-ID: goose-agent" \
  -d '{
    "q": "latest AI developments"
  }'
```

